Real Madrid manager, Zinedine Zidane, has included forward, Eden Hazard in his 19-man squad to face Celta Vigo in tonight’s La Liga fixture at the Santiago Bernabeu. Zidane had confirmed in his pre-match press conference on Saturday that Hazard, who has been out of action for three months, is ready and fit to play for the Los Blancos. Zidane’s men defeated Osasuna 4-1 in their last La Liga encounter. Real Madrid squad against Celta: Courtois, Areola, Toni Fuidias, Carvajal, Militão, Ramos, Varane, Marcelo, Mendy., Kroos, Modric, Casemiro, Valverde, Isco, Hazard, Benzema, Bale, Jović, Vinicius Jr. The match is schedule for 9 pm.